reviews_data.review_text:
Standing outside at the DMV that's a few storefronts down, I thought it convenient to walk in for a quick breakfast. I was the only one sitting down, actually I was the only one in seating area for the most part. I had ordered French Toast, eggs & potatos with a latte.
As I'm the only one sitting there, figured it wouldn't take long for my food to arrive but yet it took close to 25 minutes. That's excessive for a breakfast dish & when it's not busy.
On the upside, the food was good but as I write this review, I do feel my stomach not sitting well with my first meal of the day. Not sure I'll return.

Also they had my food to go which is all & good but I didn't ask for take out nor was the question asked so there's that.
I had an iced latte and it was delicious. Greta place to grab a drink while waiting for DMV ticket too. Relaxed and friendly atmosphere

At Passion Café and Pastry, the customer service sparkles as brightly as the food shines. Every staff member treats you like royalty — warm smiles, flawless attention, and a genuine passion for making your visit unforgettable.

⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Feels Like Home, Tastes Like Heaven
Every bite at Passion Café and Pastry is a hug for your taste buds rich, fresh, and bursting with love. Paired with the kind of warmth and care that makes you feel like family, it’s a dining experience you’ll crave forever.

⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Absolutely Unmatched
Passion Café and Pastry isn’t just a restaurant — it’s pure magic on a plate. Flavors so divine they could stop time, service that feels like a warm embrace, and an atmosphere you never want to leave. Hands down, the best restaurant in the universe.

Today, my husband, our 3-year-old, and I stopped into a café after lunch next door. The name states “café & pastry,” but I noticed they also served savory food, such as fried chicken, which explained the slightly smoky atmosphere inside.

I ordered a coffee, my husband chose a chocolate chip cookie, and we selected macaroons for our child. The barista didn't wear gloves but did use tongs to retrieve the items from the pastry display case. While waiting for my coffee, I looked more closely at the display case and noticed three pieces of cake on the top shelf that had visible mold.

When the barista handed me my coffee, I quietly informed her so as not to cause a scene, mentioning that the cakes had mold. She explained that those cakes were just for display. I pointed out they were in the same case as the other items. She said that the other pastries were baked fresh the day before. I again expressed concern that the moldy cakes were still in the same confined case as the other treats, without any separation. She just looked at me. I said 'okay' nonchalantly and walked back to my family.

For a business that displayed a health code rating of 100, it's concerning that they don't know mold is an airborne contaminant that poses health risks. Having molding items in the same display case as the items you sell to customers, is not okay.

Do not really understand how this establishment has such a good rating. Service was subpar, took a while until someone was able to take our order. The food was lackluster, bacon was burnt, eggs were unsalted, sausage was still raw in the middle, the grilled cheese was the worst part of it all. The only saving grace was the beverages and the carrot cake. I personally will not be coming again.
Food was good… the floors were very dirty..

I had three fried chicken wings, collard greens, macaroni & cheese and yams. Everything was seasoned to perfection. My daughter had three fried chicken wings and french toast.The food was hot and service was on point! I highly recommend it.
From the Mac to the baked chicken so flavorful. Chicken was delicious definitely going back appreciate the great service and food !! Keep doing what you guys doing !!!!!!love it

My own experience was unfortunate. My sister and I both went in expecting to find a place to chill out for an hour with a nice drink and treat but we got there, walked in.. chairs are on the tables and the employees in the back look up at us and keep talking to themselves until I greet them from the counter. They say hi and continue talking to themselves and doing dishes or something? Either way we're grateful for that aspect because the food looked old and gross and we were worried the drinks would come out janky. Did not try anything. Vibes were gross on everything.
This was all around 2 in the afternoon.
Completely opposite representation from their pictures online.
Like I said.. just unfortunate. That was our experience and view points.
I guess the highlight was the dollar I found crumpled up outside in the parking lot?
reviews_data.owner_answer:
I personally remember greeting you and your sister when you entered the café around 2 PM that day. Our café was open, and the chairs were only placed on some tables temporarily during a mid-day floor wipe — not an indication that we were closed. I also take pride in personally preparing fresh food and drinks daily, and we never serve anything old EVER.

I understand you mentioned not trying anything from our menu, so it’s surprising to hear comments about the food being “gross” when nothing was sampled. We respect all opinions, but it’s also important that feedback reflects actual experience

reviews_data.review_text:
After waiting in the never ending DMV line, it was such a relief to find a spot where I could grab both breakfast and lunch without missing my place. I started with the Shrimp and Grits creamy, flavorful, and cooked just right. Later, I ordered a Grilled Cheese with fries, and it hit the spot perfectly.

The atmosphere was cozy and inviting. The soft instrumental music playing in the background added a calm, relaxing vibe, and the space itself felt so comfortable. Great food, peaceful ambiance, and convenience all in one definitely made my DMV trip more bearable!

It looked like it would’ve been good online ITS NOT ! trust me save your self the trip everything was disgusting from the salmon patties to the danishes to the muffins , if I could rate 0 stars I would the skillet my eggs and were cooked in must’ve not been cleaned because they were black , I just knew I found me a lil go to spot NEVER AGAIN IN MY LIFE I literally feel sick to my stomach writing this , mind you the stuff they say they have they don’t have when you get there like smoothies and potatoes !
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We’re truly sorry to hear that your experience didn’t meet expectations. At Passion’s Café & Pastry, we take pride in our food, cleanliness, and service, so your feedback is taken seriously—regardless of the tone it’s delivered in.

That said, some of your comments caught us by surprise. We strive to maintain transparency with our menu, and if an item is unavailable, we make every effort to communicate that clearly. Regarding your concerns with the food and kitchen cleanliness, we’d have appreciated the opportunity to address them on the spot, as we have strict standards WE STAND BY DAILY .

While your visit was not what either of us hoped for, we wish you all the best in finding a spot that better suits your taste and expectations.

reviews_data.review_text: Always looking to support local small businesses. I was excited to try this spot. Coffee taste burnt, had coffee grounds in it and was way too sweet. Muffin was delicious! Unfortunately while there it seemed that something had burned in the cafe so it was smokey and smelled like burned food. May try again but needs some work.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We truly appreciate your support of local small businesses—it means the world to us. We’re glad you enjoyed the muffin, as we take great pride in our baked goods.

As for the coffee, taste can definitely be subjective, and we understand that sweetness levels vary by preference. We’d be happy to adjust it to your liking on a future visit. The brief smokiness you experienced was the result of a minor hiccup in the kitchen that was quickly resolved, though we understand how it may have affected your first impression.

We’re always working to improve, and we’d love the chance to give you a more well-rounded experience next time. Thanks again for stopping by and sharing your thoughts.

reviews_data.review_text: Fantastic little gem. We ordered the easy like Sunday morning latte, mini cookie butter muffin, and bacon, egg and cheese on everything bagel… Delicious! This will be my new go to when I am craving a weekend brunch spot.

I was eager to support this small business, but I was left unimpressed. The small space is well decorated/ looks trendy and clean. My personal customer service experience was very friendly once the cashier got off of her phone to look at us. The coffee left much to be desired however and tasted mostly like cheap syrup and watered down coffee. It tasted like a hot latte that was made iced simply by pouring it over not enough ice, resulting in the melting. The price was pretty steep to have a drink with nothing special & the place needs better ventilation as the grease is very thick in the air. All of my clothes and hair smelled like grease / kitchen smoke after spending 10 minutes here which has never happened to me at a coffee / breakfast joint. I cannot speak on the pastries as I did not try them, but I will say they are very visually beautiful.

18$ dollars for a Bacon egg and cheese bagel and a macchiato is CRAZY. For one person too.

They are nice people but insanely expensive.

Takes a while to get your order as well. Only one cook in the back.
Wonderful customer service

What a gem in Mt. Holly! The hostess is a sweetheart, and is very fun to chat with. What a warm and welcoming environment! A solid variety of coffee options, and some tasty food to boot! Their “make your own breakfast” bowl was delish; I enjoyed the hash browns, eggs, cheese, spinach, & avocado. They have these little cutie blueberry muffins, too, which are a sweet treat. The cinnamon pinwheel hit the spot, and I’m stoked to share this baklava with my fam. It’s my brother’s family’s fave spot to eat breakfast sammies! The pastry selection is unique; they even have beignets & macrons. The pink and green decor w/ the plants is cute. Overall, such a delight to enjoy & begin my day with! Come check it out, y’all, they’re a great locally owned and operated restaurant!
Mt. Holly should do them more justice with advertising by the road; since the shopping area in which they’re located is pushed back a ways, it’s harder to see their storefront, which does them a disservice because they’re so great.
Thank you, Passion’s Cafe & Pastry, for making my visit to town so positive! Lookin’ forward to trying the rest of your menu! Y’all have a blessed day. 💗💕💗💕💗

reviews_data.review_text: I got a latte and a sausage, egg, cheese on a sesame bagel. The food was okay. There was only one person working, taking orders and doing the cooking so service was very slow.   There are these horrible flickering fluorescent lights. I would suggest swapping them out, it would make a huge difference. Also more art, plants, and some comfy chairs would give this place an older and more established feel. Adding darker colors would help with the ambiance too. Lastly, I didn’t receive a coffee cup sleeve and since my coffee was hot I couldn’t pick it up and sip it while my order was being made. This is clearly a new business, probably owner operated, I think there is great potential but definitely some improvements needed.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for stopping by Christopher. We appreciate all feedback, and we are carefully taking your review into consideration. We hope to see you again ⭐️

reviews_data.review_text: This was my first time in, and I'll definitely go back. The vanilla latte was delicious but could have been hotter. The young lady that made my latte was very sweet. However, the customer service was lacking a bit. I would love to have known more about the business and their offerings, but there wasn't much interaction with the employees. The French toast muffin is incredible! It's not too sweet and tasted just like French toast. I would appreciate napkins being out for customers and maybe not use so much bleach when cleaning the floors. I wanted to dine in, but the smell was too strong. I think this place could definitely be a staple in the community.
Awesome new spot ! Great desserts!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for stopping by. Come again 🔥

I recently visited this cafe, and it exceeded all my expectations! From the moment I walked in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting, with just the right blend of modern decor and cozy charm. The cleanliness was impeccable, every corner of the space was spotless, which added to the overall comfort of the experience.

The staff were professional, friendly, and attentive without being overbearing. They made me feel welcome and were happy to answer my questions about the menu. The coffee was outstanding—rich, flavorful, and perfectly brewed and paired beautifully with the freshly made pastries and light bites. It’s clear this cafe values its customers and takes pride in its service. Whether you’re looking for a place to relax, work, or catch up with friends, this is the perfect spot. I’ll definitely be back soon! Highly recommended.

reviews_data.review_text: I got a latte and a sausage, egg, cheese on a sesame bagel. The food was okay. There was only one person working, taking orders and doing the cooking so service was very slow.   There are these horrible flickering fluorescent lights. I would suggest swapping them out, it would make a huge difference. Also more art, plants, and some comfy chairs would give this place an older and more established feel. Adding darker colors would help with the ambiance too. Lastly, I didn’t receive a coffee cup sleeve and since my coffee was hot I couldn’t pick it up and sip it while my order was being made. This is clearly a new business, probably owner operated, I think there is great potential but definitely some improvements needed.

Perfect Spot for Coffee and Conversation

I recently visited this cafe, and it exceeded all my expectations! From the moment I walked in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting, with just the right blend of modern decor and cozy charm. The cleanliness was impeccable, every corner of the space was spotless, which added to the overall comfort of the experience.

The staff were professional, friendly, and attentive without being overbearing. They made me feel welcome and were happy to answer my questions about the menu. The coffee was outstanding—rich, flavorful, and perfectly brewed and paired beautifully with the freshly made pastries and light bites. I also had the Philly and chicken cheese sandwiches and they were delicious with perfect serving sizes. Can’t beat the pricing!

It’s clear this cafe values its customers and takes pride in its service. Whether you’re looking for a place to relax, work, or catch up with friends, this is the perfect spot. I’ll definitely be back soon! Highly recommended.
